6}, {\"ngram\": \"suit\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty, 29, has won two silver medals in France, finishing second in both the 100m breaststroke and 4x100m relay medley.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8501604862058423, \"rank\": 0.16819469336400758, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 259}, {\"ngram\": \"two silver medals\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"both the 100m breaststroke and 4x100m relay medley\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's taken his overall Olympic medal tally to six, despitetesting positive for Covid-19during the Games.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his overall Olympic medal tally\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 419}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But now Peaty has called for swimming to fall in line with other authorities.\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peaty\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"other authorities\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 559}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's got to.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 574, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think the IOC has to give back more to the athletes now,\\\" he toldinews.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1438659804102466e-24, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And so they should.\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 670, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are the entertainment.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the entertainment\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 695}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think a phone (Samsung have provided every athlete at the Games with a new phone) and the Village is enough - and the athletes are waking up to that.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 0.9996722342572281, \"rank\": 0.00032764953686642486, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a phone\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"every athlete\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 756}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 760, \"to\": 769}, {\"ngram\": \"a new phone\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"the Village\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But that's a very complex question with very complex answers, because I know the governing bodies are funding that at the moment.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 987, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very complex question\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"very complex answers\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"the governing bodies\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But World Aquatics has more than enough money to go around.\\\"\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1048, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\